{"id": "duc04-testb-18:2#7", "contents": "Livingston's resignation was seen as a drastic action, with some hoping it would prompt Republicans to reconsider the impeachment of Clinton. Rep. Paul Kanjorski, D-Pa., noted that the House was \"starting to offer up sacrificial lambs to whatever terrible disease this is.\" Rep. Dick Gephardt of Missouri, the Democratic leader, praised Livingston as a \"worthy, good and honorable man\" and said his resignation was a grave mistake. Gephardt urged his colleagues to \"step back from the abyss\" and reject resignation, impeachment, and \"vicious self-righteousness.\""}
